  "title": "HR Business Operation - Data Admin (Ref 26327)",
  "description": "<p>Responsibilities<br />• Work closely with HR practitioners to maintain integrity of master data stored in e-HR by supporting data profiling, data patching/rectifications/correction and reporting<br />• Provide analysis and consultation services to address operational issues, provide resolution to data problems and perform data rectifications<br />• Coordinate with the data owner to perform the deletion and insertion of HR events sequentially to ensure data integrity.<br />• Prepare data reports and statistics to present to Authority for review and endorsement<br />• Updates of documentation (i.e. SOP, Data Catalogue)<br /><br />Requirements<br />• At least a Diploma/Degree in Computer Science, Information System, Science, Engineering or Equivalent.<br />• At least 2 years of working experience in information technology.<br />• Experience in SAP HCM ERP is preferred.<br />• Experience in operation support including end user support, troubleshooting and testing is preferred.<br />• SQL working experience and competent in SQL Programming is preferred.</p><p>Required Competencies<br />• Good knowledge of information technology, especially in the areas of SAP HCM ERP or HCM SaaS.<br />• Good understanding of the data design in SAP HCM ERP or HCM SaaS.<br />• Demonstrated competency in investigating and identifying causes of issues, and able to propose solutions to rectify the issue.<br />• Proficiency in SQL programming is preferred.<br />• Competent in applying Microsoft Excel functions.</p><p></p><p>Licence no: 12C6060</p>",
